@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Identity
@using LabProject.Areas.Identity.Data

@inject SignInManager<ApplicationUser> SignInManager

@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "About Us";
    Layout = SignInManager.IsSignedIn(User) ? "_Layout_Dashboard" : "_Layout";
}


<div class="container section-py mt-5">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <h4 class="section-title"><span class="position-relative fw-extrabold z-1">About</span> Us</h4>
            <p>
                At Moneymind, we believe that personal finance should be simple, engaging, and tailored to your lifestyle. Our mission is to provide individuals with a comprehensive yet easy-to-use tool to track and optimize their budgets, helping them take control of their financial future.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-8">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <div class="perk-card">
                        <h4 class="highlight_heading">Our <strong>Mission</strong></h4>
                        <p>Our mission is to empower individuals to make informed financial decisions by providing them with intuitive and powerful tools. We strive to simplify personal finance and make it accessible to everyone, regardless of their financial background.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="perk-card">
                        <h4 class="highlight_heading">
                                Our <strong>Vision</strong>
                        </h4>
                        
                        <p>We envision a world where everyone has the knowledge and resources to achieve their financial goals. We aim to be the leading platform for personal finance management, trusted by users worldwide for its simplicity, effectiveness, and innovation.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <section class="bg-body section-py landing-reviews">
        <div class="container ">
            <div class="row align-items-center gx-0 gy-4 g-lg-5 mb-5 pb-md-5">
                <div class="text-end col-md-6 col-lg-5 col-xl-3">
                    <span class="badge bg-label-primary">Our team</span>
                    <h4 class="mt-3"> We do our best for you</h4>
                    <p class="text-muted">Who's building this great project?</p>
                </div>

                <div class="d-flex gap-10 col-md-6 col-lg-7 col-xl-9">

                    

                    <div class="card h-100">
                        <div class="card-body text-body d-flex flex-column justify-content-between h-100">
                            <div class="w-25 mb-2 justify-content-end">
                                <img src="~/assets/images/piotr.jpg" alt="Avatar" class="rounded-circle img-fluid">
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <h6 class="mb-0">Piotr Matla</h6>
                                <p class="small text-muted mb-0">Software Developer</p>
                            </div>
                            <p>
                                Piotr is the driving force behind Moneymind, shaping the vision for the future of personal finance management. He is passionate about creating tools that make managing money easier for everyone.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="card h-auto">
                        <div class="card-body text-body d-flex flex-column justify-content-between h-100">
                            <div class="w-25 mb-2">
                                <img src="~/assets/images/klaudia.jpg" alt="Avatar" class="rounded-circle img-fluid">
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <h6 class="mb-0">
                                    Klaudia Marszałek
                                </h6>
                                <p class="small text-muted mb-0">Software Developer</p>
                            </div>
                            <p>
                                Klaudia brings a wealth of knowledge in software development and engineering, overseeing the technical side of Moneymind.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    

                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section-py">
        <h4 class="fw-bold my-4">Our Study Case & Challenges</h4>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <p>Developing Moneymind presented several challenges that pushed our team to rethink how we design budget management tools. One of the primary obstacles was how to make a complex system, such as personal finance tracking, feel simple and approachable without sacrificing power or flexibility.</p>
                <p>Early user feedback indicated that many existing apps were either too complicated for casual users or lacked the depth needed by more advanced users. Our solution was to create a flexible structure that allowed for both basic and advanced features. The result was a modular system where users could customize their experience based on their financial needs.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <ul class="list-unstyled">
                    <li class="mb-2"><strong>Balancing Simplicity and Power:</strong> Our initial design was either too simple, offering limited features, or too complex, confusing our users. After extensive testing, we refined the app’s interface to be both user-friendly and feature-rich, with customizable options for both beginners and experts.</li>
                    <li class="mb-2"><strong>Real-Time Updates:</strong> One of the most important features we added was real-time expense tracking. It was critical that users could see updates as soon as they made purchases. We integrated bank feeds and a smart categorization system, which automatically tagged expenses into categories like food, entertainment, and utilities.</li>
                    <li><strong>Personalized Savings Goals:</strong> Our users wanted to not only track their spending but also have an easy way to save for goals such as vacations, emergency funds, and big purchases. We designed the savings feature to be motivational, showing users their progress towards goals with visual charts and reminders.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="d-flex flex-wrap justify-content-center w-100">
        <div class="w-50 text-center">
            <span class="badge bg-label-primary mb-2">Outlook</span>
            <h4 class="fw-bold mb-4">Results & Future</h4>
            <p class="highlight_text mb-5">Through multiple iterations and user testing, Moneymind transformed from a basic budget tracker into a powerful financial assistant that adapts to individual needs. With over <strong>10,000 active users</strong>, we’ve received positive feedback for the app’s <strong>clean design, ease of use,</strong> and the ability to offer actionable insights into spending habits.</p>
            <p class="highlight_text">We’re constantly improving Moneymind by adding new features based on user feedback, including a debt tracking module, investment portfolio integration, and enhanced reporting tools. Our goal is to continue helping users <strong>make smarter, more informed financial decisions.</strong></p>
        </div>
        
    </section>

</div>
